# Stock Tracker - Environment Variables

## Backend (Render.com)

### Required Environment Variables
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:password@ep-xxx-xxx-123456.us-east-2.aws.neon.tech/stocktracker?sslmode=require
REDIS_URL=redis://default:xxxxx@xxx.upstash.io:6379
PORT=10000
ALLOWED_HOSTS=.onrender.com

### Python Settings
PYTHON_VERSION=3.12

## Frontend (Vercel)

### Build-time Variables (VITE_ prefix exposed to client)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://stock-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/v1
VITE_API_TARGET=https://stock-tracker-api.onrender.com

### Runtime Variables (private, server-side only)
# VERCEL_GIT_COMMIT_SHA (auto-set by Vercel)
# NODE_ENV (auto-set by Vercel)

## How to Set in Vercel Dashboard

1. Go to your Vercel project → Settings → Environment Variables
2. Add:
   - Name: `VITE_API_BASE_URL`
   - Value: Your Render backend URL, e.g., `https://stock-tracker-api.onrender.com/api/v1`
   - Environments: Production, Preview, Development (all)

3. Redeploy after adding variables (or Vercel auto-deploys)

## How to Set in Render.com Dashboard

1. Go to your Web Service → Environment
2. Add all DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, PORT, ALLOWED_HOSTS
3. Redeploy (or auto-deploy after changes)